464
00:19:33,694 --> 00:19:34,651
SHE'S DEAD.

465
00:19:36,784 --> 00:19:38,002
OH...

466
00:19:38,046 --> 00:19:39,221
I'M SO SORRY.

467
00:19:39,265 --> 00:19:40,614
IT'S OKAY.

468
00:19:40,657 --> 00:19:42,268
SHE'S NOT, LIKE,
COMPLETELY GONE.

469
00:19:42,311 --> 00:19:43,356
BECAUSE...

470
00:19:44,008 --> 00:19:44,792
SHE COMES BACK.

471
00:19:46,054 --> 00:19:46,881
SHE COMES BACK?

472
00:19:47,360 --> 00:19:48,578
A LOT.

473
00:19:48,622 --> 00:19:49,884
[WIND BLOWING]

474
00:19:50,406 --> 00:19:51,538
[GASPS]

475
00:19:55,716 --> 00:19:56,717
THAT WASN'T HER.

476
00:20:03,332 --> 00:20:04,768
[GREGG]: OKAY, EVERYBODY,

477
00:20:04,812 --> 00:20:06,814
IF YOU COULD BE AN ANIMAL,
ANY ANIMAL,

478
00:20:08,032 --> 00:20:09,556
WHAT ANIMAL
WOULD YOU CHOOSE TO BE?

479
00:20:10,687 --> 00:20:11,775
DELORES,

480
00:20:11,819 --> 00:20:13,037
WOULD YOU LIKE TO GO FIRST?

481
00:20:13,081 --> 00:20:14,343
OH, I'D LIKE TO GO LAST,

482
00:20:14,387 --> 00:20:15,518
IF YOU WOULDN'T MIND.

483
00:20:15,562 --> 00:20:16,737
OKAY, I THINK
THAT'D BE APPROPRIATE.

484
00:20:16,780 --> 00:20:18,260
THANKS, GREGG.

485
00:20:18,304 --> 00:20:19,392
MILLIE,
HOW ABOUT YOU?

486
00:20:21,611 --> 00:20:23,352
I THINK I'LL GO
RIGHT BEFORE DELORES.

487
00:20:24,527 --> 00:20:26,834
DO YOU THINK
THAT'S APPROPRIATE?

488
00:20:26,877 --> 00:20:28,052
[GEORGE]:  <i>WHO GIVES A SHIT?</i>

489
00:20:28,096 --> 00:20:29,228
I REALLY DO, GREGG.

490
00:20:30,664 --> 00:20:31,926
CAN I START?

491
00:20:32,970 --> 00:20:34,102
SURE, TODD.

492
00:20:34,145 --> 00:20:35,059
YEAH,
THAT'D BE GREAT.

493
00:20:36,409 --> 00:20:39,281
IF I WERE AN ANIMAL,
I THINK I WOULD BE A CRAB.

494
00:20:40,239 --> 00:20:41,327
NOT AN ANIMAL.

495
00:20:41,370 --> 00:20:42,850
MILLIE.

496
00:20:42,893 --> 00:20:43,851
WELL, IT'S NOT.
IT'S A CRUSTACEAN.

497
00:20:46,201 --> 00:20:47,463
WHAT?

498
00:20:47,507 --> 00:20:49,030
WELL, AT LEAST I'M LISTENING.

499
00:20:50,640 --> 00:20:52,338
I'M SORRY.
A CRAB'S AN ANIMAL.

500
00:20:52,381 --> 00:20:54,644
IT'S A BIG, FURRY,
WARM-BLOODED BEAST

501
00:20:54,688 --> 00:20:57,125
THAT SLEEPS IN COCKTAIL SAUCE.

502
00:20:57,168 --> 00:21:00,955
MILLIE, THIS IS AN EXERCISE
ABOUT REVEALING YOURSELF

503
00:21:00,998 --> 00:21:02,522
TO YOUR CO-WORKERS.

504
00:21:02,565 --> 00:21:04,132
NOW, WE ALL FIND
THINGS TO HIDE BEHIND

505
00:21:04,175 --> 00:21:05,655
AT THE OFFICE.

506
00:21:05,699 --> 00:21:08,832
YOU KNOW, OUR CUBICLES,
OUR TELEPHONES,
OUR DEADLINES...

507
00:21:08,876 --> 00:21:10,181
OUR SARCASM.

508
00:21:10,225 --> 00:21:11,574
WE ALL FIND WAYS

509
00:21:11,618 --> 00:21:13,054
NOT TO GET TO KNOW
THE PEOPLE

510
00:21:13,097 --> 00:21:15,186
THAT WE RELY ON THE MOST.

511
00:21:15,230 --> 00:21:18,538
OUT HERE IN THE WILD,
THERE'S NO PLACE
TO HIDE, OKAY?

512
00:21:18,581 --> 00:21:19,756
SO I THINK THAT WE SHOULD ALL

513
00:21:19,800 --> 00:21:22,281
TRY TO GET TO KNOW
TODD THE CRAB.

514
00:21:22,716 --> 00:21:24,674
WHOO-HOO!

515
00:21:24,718 --> 00:21:25,936
[GEORGE]: <i>
I BET TODD HAS CRABS.</i>

516
00:21:27,155 --> 00:21:28,983
TODD, PLEASE.

517
00:21:29,026 --> 00:21:33,857
I ALWAYS FEEL...
AS IF I'M MOVING SIDEWAYS.

518
00:21:33,901 --> 00:21:36,425
MOTHERFUCKING...
I AM VICIOUSLY FUCKED.

519
00:21:36,469 --> 00:21:38,340
BASTARD HELL...

520
00:21:38,384 --> 00:21:39,515
I AM VICIOUSLY FUCKED.

521
00:21:39,559 --> 00:21:40,951
NO, NOT YOU, DARLING.

522
00:21:40,995 --> 00:21:42,475
UNLESS YOU'RE INTERESTED,
IN WHICH CASE--

523
00:21:42,518 --> 00:21:44,215
NO? WELL, PISS OFF, THEN.

524
00:21:44,259 --> 00:21:45,695
FUCK OFF. OH, JESUS CHRIST.

525
00:21:45,739 --> 00:21:47,741
OH, BOLLOCKS.
KIFFANY! KIFFANY.

526
00:21:49,003 --> 00:21:50,918
HEY, THERE.

527
00:21:50,961 --> 00:21:52,876
LISTEN, HAVE YOU FOUND
A LITTLE POST-IT?

528
00:21:52,920 --> 00:21:54,922
YOU KNOW,
THE LITTLE YELLOW ONES
WITH WRITING ON?

529
00:21:54,965 --> 00:21:56,358
LIKE THE KIND YOU PEOPLE
ALWAYS PLAY WITH?

530
00:21:56,402 --> 00:21:57,577
YES, YES, YES.
EXACTLY. EXACTLY.

531
00:21:57,620 --> 00:21:59,448
NO. IS THIS ONE
PARTICULARLY IMPORTANT?

532
00:21:59,492 --> 00:22:01,581
I DON'T BOLLOCKING
WELL KNOW, DO I?

533
00:22:01,624 --> 00:22:03,365
JESUS CHRIST, I AM FUCKED.

534
00:22:03,409 --> 00:22:05,106
MOVE.

535
00:22:05,149 --> 00:22:08,152
SHIT. BOLLOCKS.
FUCKING BOLLOCKS!

536
00:22:08,196 --> 00:22:10,067
OKAY, WELL, THAT'S IT.
I'M FUCKING FUCKED, AREN'T I?

537
00:22:10,111 --> 00:22:11,634
I'M BOLLOCKING
VICIOUSLY FUCKED.

538
00:22:11,678 --> 00:22:12,896
ROYALLY FUCKED, I AM.

539
00:22:14,333 --> 00:22:15,725
[MUSIC PLAYING]

540
00:22:18,902 --> 00:22:20,730
WELL, THAT IS
MOST INTERESTING.

541
00:22:20,774 --> 00:22:22,079
I JUST ASSUMED
ALL THOSE STORIES

542
00:22:22,123 --> 00:22:25,256
ABOUT DEGRADING
INITIATION RITUALS WERE TRUE.

543
00:22:25,300 --> 00:22:26,997
NO ONE HAS TO KILL ANYONE
TO GET INTO THE BALD EAGLES.

544
00:22:27,041 --> 00:22:29,565
WE FIGURE
THE RIGHT MEMBERS
COME AT THE RIGHT TIME.

545
00:22:29,609 --> 00:22:31,959
TREACH HERE BECAME ONE
AFTER SOMEONE HAD READ A POEM
HE WROTE IN A BIKER MAG.

546
00:22:32,568 --> 00:22:35,266
OPEN VERSE
FOR THE OPEN ROAD.

547
00:22:35,310 --> 00:22:36,485
HEAR, HEAR.

548
00:22:36,529 --> 00:22:37,747
[ALL]: HEAR!

549
00:22:41,272 --> 00:22:43,492
I DO LOVE A REAL MAN
OF LETTERS.

550
00:22:43,536 --> 00:22:45,320
SO WHY ARE YOU GUYS
CALLED THE BALD EAGLES?

551
00:22:45,364 --> 00:22:47,148
WE DON'T WEAR HELMETS.
FUCKS WITH OUR HAIR.

552
00:22:48,628 --> 00:22:50,020
I JUST THINK
A MAN SHOULD CHOOSE

553
00:22:50,064 --> 00:22:51,718
HOW CLOSE TO DEATH
HE WANTS TO LIVE.

554
00:22:51,761 --> 00:22:52,849
CLOSER THAN YOU THINK, TINY.

555
00:22:58,289 --> 00:23:00,074
DAISY, DAISY,
I NEED YOUR HELP.

556
00:23:00,117 --> 00:23:01,423
NOW.

557
00:23:02,685 --> 00:23:04,295
YOU WANT TO TAKE YOUR--

558
00:23:04,339 --> 00:23:05,993
YOU WANT TO TAKE YOUR
HANDS OFF THE LADY?

559
00:23:11,346 --> 00:23:12,782
I'M IN TROUBLE.

560
00:23:12,826 --> 00:23:14,523
THIS IS MASON.
HE'S OKAY, FELLAS,

561
00:23:14,567 --> 00:23:15,698
JUST NOT VERY WELL
BROUGHT UP IS ALL.

562
00:23:15,742 --> 00:23:17,004
NO, I'M NOT.

563
00:23:17,047 --> 00:23:19,006
THE ONLY THING WE HATE
WORSE THAN BAD MANNERS

564
00:23:19,049 --> 00:23:20,616
IS THE GODDAMN
FASCIST HELMET LAW.

565
00:23:20,660 --> 00:23:21,748
BARE HEADS TILL WE'RE DEAD.

566
00:23:21,791 --> 00:23:23,097
TILL WE'RE DEAD!

567
00:23:23,140 --> 00:23:24,446
BARE HEADS.

568
00:23:24,490 --> 00:23:26,013
YEAH! YEAH!YEAH, RIGHT, RIGHT,
RIGHT, RIGHT.

569
00:23:26,056 --> 00:23:27,144
BETTER DEAD THAN NOT.

570
00:23:27,536 --> 00:23:29,059
WHAT?

571
00:23:33,324 --> 00:23:34,543
I LOST MY POST-IT.

572
00:23:35,762 --> 00:23:36,980
HAVE A NICE RIDE, FELLOWS.
GOT TO GO.

573
00:23:40,636 --> 00:23:42,551
SUCH A LOYAL GROUP OF PEOPLE.

574
00:23:42,595 --> 00:23:43,813
BUT SO DANGEROUS.

575
00:23:47,121 --> 00:23:48,165
[PATRONS YELLING]

576
00:23:49,297 --> 00:23:50,777
TINY!

577
00:23:55,042 --> 00:23:57,610
THOSE MOTORCYCLES,
THEY'RE DANGEROUS.

578
00:23:59,176 --> 00:24:01,091
WELL, A HELMET
WOULDN'T HAVE HELPED.

579
00:24:01,135 --> 00:24:02,441
TINY MADE A BIG MESS.

580
00:24:07,533 --> 00:24:09,056
...AND I MOVED HERE
FROM ALBANY

581
00:24:09,099 --> 00:24:10,927
WHEN SHE BROKE OFF
THE ENGAGEMENT.

582
00:24:12,015 --> 00:24:13,930
3,000 MILES
DOWN THE ROAD,

583
00:24:13,974 --> 00:24:15,149
AND I STILL CAN'T GET HER
OUT OF MY MIND.

584
00:24:15,932 --> 00:24:17,281
NO.

585
00:24:17,325 --> 00:24:19,414
WE WERE NEVER ENGAGED, FRANK.

586
00:24:19,458 --> 00:24:20,981
WE WERE TOTALLY ENGAGED.

587
00:24:21,024 --> 00:24:22,112
I GAVE YOU MY MOTHER'S RING.

588
00:24:22,156 --> 00:24:23,592
SO?

589
00:24:23,636 --> 00:24:25,072
OKAY, FRANK, FRANK,
FRANK, FRANK!

590
00:24:25,115 --> 00:24:26,682
SALLY, PLEASE.

591
00:24:28,771 --> 00:24:29,903
RIGHT. RIGHT.

592
00:24:32,166 --> 00:24:34,777
ANYWAY, THAT'S WHY
I FEEL LIKE A LEOPARD.

593
00:24:34,821 --> 00:24:37,432
BECAUSE YOU'RE STALKING HER?

594
00:24:37,476 --> 00:24:39,042
BECAUSE I CAN'T
CHANGE MY SPOTS.

595
00:24:40,000 --> 00:24:42,481
OKAY, MILLIE,
I THINK
IT'S YOUR TURN.

596
00:24:43,046 --> 00:24:44,221
UH, NO, I...

597
00:24:44,265 --> 00:24:45,962
I JUST, I--

598
00:24:46,006 --> 00:24:47,311
I DON'T REALLY...

599
00:24:51,402 --> 00:24:53,056
I'M NOT AN ANIMAL.

600
00:25:00,368 --> 00:25:02,631
[GEORGE]:  <i>THIS WAS STARTING
TO FEEL FAMILIAR...</i>

601
00:25:02,675 --> 00:25:04,415
<i>STAYING ON THE SIDELINES.</i>

602
00:25:04,459 --> 00:25:06,592
<i>CRITICIZING.
CLINGING TO THE FRINGES</i>

603
00:25:06,635 --> 00:25:09,116
<i>INSTEAD OF JUMPING
INTO THE FRAY.</i>

604
00:25:09,159 --> 00:25:11,335
<i>IT WAS LIKE WATCHING
THE ESCALATOR RUN.</i>

605
00:25:11,379 --> 00:25:13,294
<i>WHEN WOULD I STEP ON?</i>

606
00:25:13,337 --> 00:25:14,600
OKAY, DELORES,

607
00:25:14,643 --> 00:25:16,340
WELL, I GUESS
THAT JUST LEAVES YOU.

608
00:25:16,384 --> 00:25:17,646
BRING US HOME.

609
00:25:17,690 --> 00:25:19,561
WELL, UM,
I'VE ALWAYS THOUGHT--

610
00:25:19,605 --> 00:25:20,649
I'M A CAT.

611
00:25:23,391 --> 00:25:25,741
I MEAN, NOT LIKE A HOUSE CAT.

612
00:25:25,785 --> 00:25:27,090
NOT LIKE MURRAY, DELORES.

613
00:25:28,178 --> 00:25:29,484
I'M A STRAY...

614
00:25:32,008 --> 00:25:36,273
WANDERS THE STREETS, ALONE,
KIND OF DISTANT AND MEAN.

615
00:25:40,887 --> 00:25:44,804
NOT A CAT YOU'D WANT TO PET
OR BRING HOME TO YOUR KIDS.

616
00:25:44,847 --> 00:25:46,936
YOU JUST DON'T KNOW
WHERE THOSE CLAWS ARE,
YOU KNOW.

617
00:25:51,941 --> 00:25:53,552
AND I'M A BLACK CAT.

618
00:25:55,728 --> 00:26:00,036
AND I HAVE MANY, MANY LIVES.

619
00:26:04,867 --> 00:26:06,652
AND NOW YOU KNOW
WHO I AM.

620
00:26:12,135 --> 00:26:14,181
YOU'D THINK
HE'D HAVE A BETTER LOCK.

621
00:26:21,667 --> 00:26:22,972
[DAISY]: WOW.

622
00:26:23,973 --> 00:26:25,366
COLOR ME IMPRESSED.

623
00:26:29,152 --> 00:26:30,850
WELL, IF HE WRITES
THE INFORMATION

624
00:26:30,893 --> 00:26:32,112
ON OUR POST-ITS,

625
00:26:32,155 --> 00:26:34,331
HE MUST COPY IT DOWN
FROM SOMEWHERE, RIGHT?

626
00:26:34,375 --> 00:26:35,463
YEAH, BUT WHERE?

627
00:26:36,464 --> 00:26:37,987
I'LL CHECK
THE LIQUOR CABINET,

628
00:26:38,031 --> 00:26:39,467
YOU CHECK
EVERYWHERE ELSE.

629
00:26:39,510 --> 00:26:41,512
MASON, NO.
THIS IS A COVERT OPERATION.

630
00:26:41,556 --> 00:26:43,036
WE NEED TO TREAD GENTLY

631
00:26:43,079 --> 00:26:44,603
AND COVER OUR TRACKS.

632
00:26:45,734 --> 00:26:47,170
[SNIFFING]

633
00:26:47,214 --> 00:26:48,476
MM...

634
00:26:48,519 --> 00:26:51,435
OLD FARTS LIKE RUBE
ALWAYS HAVE THE BEST BOOZE.

635
00:26:51,479 --> 00:26:53,046
THEY'VE BEEN DRINKING
LONG ENOUGH

636
00:26:53,089 --> 00:26:54,656
NOT TO MESS AROUND
WITH THE CHEAP SHIT.

637
00:26:54,700 --> 00:26:56,310
HOW IS THAT HELPING?

638
00:26:58,660 --> 00:27:00,227
TAKES OFF THE EDGE.
I'M ALL EDGES RIGHT NOW.

639
00:27:00,270 --> 00:27:01,837
ALL RIGHT?

640
00:27:01,881 --> 00:27:02,795
MASON, IF HE FINDS OUT
WE WERE RUMMAGING
AROUND HERE--

641
00:27:02,838 --> 00:27:03,883
PUT THAT DOWN.

642
00:27:04,535 --> 00:27:05,711
PUT IT DOWN.

643
00:27:06,668 --> 00:27:08,191
PUT THAT... DOWN.

644
00:27:11,934 --> 00:27:13,240
THIS WAS YOUR IDEA, DAISY.

645
00:27:22,031 --> 00:27:24,730
I ONCE HAD TO HIDE
FOR HOURS IN ONE
HALF THIS SIZE

646
00:27:24,773 --> 00:27:27,558
FROM THE SHREW
OF A MRS. TYRONE POWERS,

647
00:27:27,602 --> 00:27:29,648
WHO WAS SUPPOSED TO BE
IN PALM SPRINGS.

648
00:27:29,691 --> 00:27:33,216
I WAS FORCED TO URINATE
IN A HIGHBALL GLASS.

649
00:27:33,260 --> 00:27:35,001
WHAT IS IT WITH YOU
AND THE MARRIED ONES?

650
00:27:36,132 --> 00:27:37,351
FORBIDDEN FRUIT?

651
00:27:37,394 --> 00:27:38,657
THAT WAS THEN,
AND I DON'T KNOW WHY

652
00:27:38,700 --> 00:27:39,658
YOU'RE TREATING THIS
LIKE HAPPY HOUR.

653
00:27:43,705 --> 00:27:45,141
OH, SHIT.

654
00:27:45,751 --> 00:27:47,274
SO...

655
00:27:47,317 --> 00:27:48,362
SO MANY OF THEM.

656
00:27:49,102 --> 00:27:50,233
SO MUCH MORE OF IT.

657
00:27:53,715 --> 00:27:55,978
POUR ME A DRINK, WILL YOU?

658
00:27:56,022 --> 00:27:58,198
JUST ONE. AND ONLY
TO WARM ME UP.

659
00:27:58,241 --> 00:28:00,809
YEAH, IT'LL LUBE OUR SYNAPSES
UP A BIT,

660
00:28:00,853 --> 00:28:03,420
MAKE OUR MINDS
A BIT MORE N... NIMBLE.

661
00:28:10,863 --> 00:28:12,342
WE'LL KEEP LOOKING
FOR YOUR POST-IT.

662
00:28:12,386 --> 00:28:13,213
WE'LL-- WE'LL KEEP
LOOKING. YEAH.

663
00:28:37,890 --> 00:28:39,805
WHY ARE YOU SPYING ON ME?

664
00:28:39,848 --> 00:28:42,938
I'M NOT.I WASN'T
SAYING ANYTHING.

665
00:28:42,982 --> 00:28:43,983
I DIDN'T SAY
THAT YOU WERE.

666
00:28:44,026 --> 00:28:45,201
WELL, WHY ARE YOU
HERE, THEN?

667
00:28:45,245 --> 00:28:47,116
WHY DID YOU SHOW UP
ALL OF A SUDDEN?

668
00:28:47,160 --> 00:28:49,466
WELL, WHAT HAS BEEN
YOUR EXPERIENCE

669
00:28:49,510 --> 00:28:51,207
AS TO WHY I SHOW UP
ALL OF A SUDDEN?

670
00:28:51,947 --> 00:28:53,209
OH, NO.

671
00:28:55,516 --> 00:28:57,083
YOU KNOW,
YOU DO HAVE

672
00:28:57,126 --> 00:28:59,128
ACTUAL RESPONSIBILITIES
IN THIS WORLD.

673
00:29:00,521 --> 00:29:01,957
I KNOW YOU.

674
00:29:02,001 --> 00:29:03,742
YOU'RE MILLIE'S SPONSOR.

675
00:29:03,785 --> 00:29:04,655
SO DEVOTED.

676
00:29:06,875 --> 00:29:09,443
DELORES, RIGHT?RIGHT. AND YOU'RE RUBE.

677
00:29:09,486 --> 00:29:10,618
I AM.

678
00:29:10,661 --> 00:29:13,186
IS THAT A FIRST NAME
OR LAST NAME?

679
00:29:13,229 --> 00:29:14,665
JUST RUBE.

680
00:29:14,709 --> 00:29:16,015
LIKE CHER.

681
00:29:16,058 --> 00:29:17,233
LIKE HOUDINI.

682
00:29:17,843 --> 00:29:19,540
LOVE HOUDINI.

683
00:29:19,583 --> 00:29:21,368
WOULDN'T IT HAVE BEEN FUN
TO HAVE SEEN HIM?

684
00:29:22,195 --> 00:29:23,326
[GEORGE]:  <i>SEEN HIM?</i>

685
00:29:23,370 --> 00:29:25,024
<i>RUBE PROBABLY REAPED HIM.</i>

686
00:29:26,460 --> 00:29:27,983
WHAT BRINGS YOU
OUT HERE, RUBE?

687
00:29:28,854 --> 00:29:29,942
WELL, DELORES...

688
00:29:32,074 --> 00:29:33,554
AS MUCH AS I'D LIKE
TO GET INTO THAT WITH YOU--

689
00:29:33,597 --> 00:29:35,295
UH-HUH?

690
00:29:35,338 --> 00:29:37,079
ONE OF THE "A"S OF A.A.
STANDS FOR--

691
00:29:37,123 --> 00:29:40,779
YOU DON'T WANT A DRINK,
DO YOU, MILLIE?

692
00:29:40,822 --> 00:29:42,215
ACTUALLY, I WAS REFERRING
TO THE OTHER "A".

693
00:29:43,869 --> 00:29:45,174
OH, OF COURSE.

694
00:29:47,176 --> 00:29:48,656
DELORES,
I THINK I NEED

695
00:29:48,699 --> 00:29:50,527
TO GO FOR A WALK
AND GET SOME FRESH AIR.

696
00:29:50,571 --> 00:29:51,659
WELL, YOU'RE
IN THE WOODS.

697
00:29:51,702 --> 00:29:52,486
YOU'RE SURROUNDED
BY FRESH AIR.

698
00:29:53,704 --> 00:29:55,794
I JUST...
WANT TO GO FOR A WALK.

699
00:29:56,490 --> 00:29:57,578
I NEED TO...

700
00:29:59,623 --> 00:30:02,496
COMMUNE WITH
THE SPIRITS OF THE NORTHWEST.

701
00:30:03,410 --> 00:30:05,281
YOU ARE A CAT, AREN'T YOU?

702
00:30:05,325 --> 00:30:07,631
ALONE AND MYSTERIOUS.

703
00:30:07,675 --> 00:30:09,895
MAKE SURE YOU MAKE IT BACK
FOR GHOST STORIES AND S'MORES.

704
00:30:10,634 --> 00:30:11,679
I'LL TRY.

